in the shoe store.

03:11.000 --> 03:13.501
Every fat woman
in Chicago hippos in

03:13.501 --> 03:17.167
wanting pink pumps.

03:17.167 --> 03:18.834
They think it
makes them look sexy,

03:18.834 --> 03:20.534
as if anyone
could see the shoes

03:20.534 --> 03:23.200
over the bulging flesh
of their ankles.

03:23.200 --> 03:24.834
Good morning, Al.

03:24.834 --> 03:26.100
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

03:31.267 --> 03:33.000
So, honey, you want
anything special

03:33.000 --> 03:34.667
for Valentine's Day?

03:34.667 --> 03:37.634
Yeah, but she's
wrestling in the mud,

03:37.634 --> 03:39.133
and I'm just living there.

03:39.133 --> 03:40.634
[DOORBELL RINGS]

03:40.634 --> 03:42.133
Who the hell could that be?

03:42.133 --> 03:44.467
Well, it's Valentine's Day.
Maybe it's Cupid.

03:44.467 --> 03:46.968
No, he'd never
show his face around here again

03:46.968 --> 03:48.734
after making this match.

03:48.734 --> 03:50.634
Hi, Al.

03:50.634 --> 03:53.968
You know, all you have to do
is walk outside, look around.

03:53.968 --> 03:55.601
You just know
it's Valentine's Day.

03:55.601 --> 03:56.767
What do you want?

03:56.767 --> 03:57.868
Al, I need a favor.

03:59.367 --> 04:01.300
Uh, Peggy, I need a favor.

04:01.300 --> 04:03.701
I need someplace
to hide Marcie's present.

04:03.701 --> 04:06.300
Oh, gee, Steve, what is it?

04:06.300 --> 04:08.300
You know, having Al
for a husband,

04:08.300 --> 04:10.801
I've always wondered,
what do husbands

04:10.801 --> 04:14.000
give their wives
for Valentine's Day?

04:14.000 --> 04:16.466
Well, this isn't
a fair example.

04:16.466 --> 04:18.834
See, for us, it's not just
Valentine's Day.

04:18.834 --> 04:20.601
It's our first anniversary.

04:20.601 --> 04:23.334
Oh, Al...

04:23.334 --> 04:27.300
Leave me alone.

04:27.300 --> 04:30.100
Yes, well, uh,
would you hide this for me?

04:30.100 --> 04:34.667
Sure. I'll
hide it upstairs.

04:34.667 --> 04:37.434
Let me save you
some wear and tear

04:37.434 --> 04:39.367
on your nails
and teeth.

04:39.367 --> 04:41.267
See, the first anniversary
is paper,

04:41.267 --> 04:43.267
and since paper
isn't all that romantic,

04:43.267 --> 04:45.634
I got her tickets for two
to Hawaii.

04:45.634 --> 04:48.234
Oh, now, please don't tell her.
I want it to be a surprise.

04:48.234 --> 04:51.133
Don't worry.
I can keep a secret.

04:51.133 --> 04:53.133
Oh, by the way, Al,

04:53.133 --> 04:55.968
that little rubber doughnut
you ordered came in yesterday.

04:55.968 --> 04:57.667
Al's got 'rhoids,
you know.

05:01.968 --> 05:07.467
Well, you're obviously
sitting pretty.

05:07.467 --> 05:09.434
So, what are you
getting Peggy

05:09.434 --> 05:11.000
for Valentine's Day?

05:11.000 --> 05:12.968
Fur, jewels, a car?

05:12.968 --> 05:15.968
If it was
only that easy.

05:15.968 --> 05:19.667
I'm going to have
sex with her.

05:19.667 --> 05:21.667
It's kind of a tradition.

05:21.667 --> 05:24.667
Every Valentine's Day,
I climb those stairs,

05:24.667 --> 05:27.334
you know, walk
the last mile, and, uh...

05:27.334 --> 05:32.267
slam-dunk her one.

05:32.267 --> 05:33.667
It's a spin
through hell for me,

05:33.667 --> 05:35.501
but she
seems to like it.

05:35.501 --> 05:37.767
I only pray
that after 16 years,

05:37.767 --> 05:39.000
Marcie and I will
have

05:39.000 --> 05:42.100
that kind of magic
between us.

05:42.100 --> 05:43.834
Steve, if it was magic,

05:43.834 --> 05:46.100
I could do it from down
here in front of the TV.

05:58.801 --> 06:00.834
