06:00.834 --> 06:02.133
Hi, Peggy.

06:02.133 --> 06:04.133
I waited till Steve left home.

06:04.133 --> 06:05.634
I need your help.

06:05.634 --> 06:08.434
What can I get him
for our anniversary?

06:08.434 --> 06:12.634
Well, don't get him
two tickets to Hawaii.

06:12.634 --> 06:16.734
That's what he got you.
It's a surprise.

06:16.734 --> 06:20.634
He got me tickets to Hawaii?

06:20.634 --> 06:22.133
Damn him!

06:22.133 --> 06:25.667
He's so irritating,
getting me the perfect gift.

06:25.667 --> 06:29.167
Now I have to get him
something just as great.

06:29.167 --> 06:31.901
What a weenie.
God, I hate him.

06:31.901 --> 06:35.133
Sure you do.
He's your husband.

06:35.133 --> 06:36.267
Yeah, well,

06:36.267 --> 06:38.601
I still have to find him
something really good--

06:38.601 --> 06:41.934
something personal,
something romantic,

06:41.934 --> 06:43.434
something that symbolizes

06:43.434 --> 06:46.367
the depth and purity
of our relationship.

06:46.367 --> 06:49.467
You could jump naked
out of a cake.

06:49.467 --> 06:51.534
Yeah. That says it all!

06:51.534 --> 06:52.934
But who would know

06:52.934 --> 06:55.400
where to find something
so kinky?

06:55.400 --> 06:59.300
Cakes a Poppin'.

06:59.300 --> 07:02.300
Just ask for Leif.
Here's their number.

07:02.300 --> 07:05.300
Oh, and when you pay,
have them stamp my card.

07:05.300 --> 07:07.801
Two more, I get one free.

07:07.801 --> 07:09.300
I'll do it.

07:09.300 --> 07:11.801
I know.
The cake can say,

07:11.801 --> 07:13.667
"Take me.
I'm yours."

07:13.667 --> 07:15.133
Steve will love it.
Thanks, Peg.

07:15.133 --> 07:18.400
So, do you know
what Al's getting you?

07:18.400 --> 07:21.300
Oh, yeah. Same thing he
gets me every year.

07:21.300 --> 07:24.067
He's going to slam-dunk
me a quick one.

07:27.901 --> 07:29.300
Of course,
those are his words.

07:29.300 --> 07:30.300
I mean, in reality,

07:30.300 --> 07:34.834
it's more like
a foul shot.

07:34.834 --> 07:39.501
You know, he takes
a deep breath and scores.

07:39.501 --> 07:40.667
Sure, it's worth a point,

07:40.667 --> 07:43.968
but it will never make
the highlight reel.

07:43.968 --> 07:48.200
It's like your honeymoon
never ended.

07:48.200 --> 07:50.200
But as long as he
tells you he loves you,

07:50.200 --> 07:51.767
I guess that's all
that really matters.

07:51.767 --> 07:53.501
Actually, Al says,

07:53.501 --> 07:57.601
"There. That
should hold you."

07:57.601 --> 07:59.100
But you know Al.
You know,

07:59.100 --> 08:01.601
he just has difficulty
saying certain things,

08:01.601 --> 08:04.133
Like "I love you,"
"thank you,"

08:04.133 --> 08:07.334
and "Look out.
There's a car coming."

08:07.334 --> 08:10.801
Oh, bunk.
You live in this hovel,

08:10.801 --> 08:13.801
