10:28.534 --> 10:31.300
Are we going
to do it twice?

10:31.300 --> 10:32.567
Peg, remember,

10:32.567 --> 10:36.701
a smart mouth
is a lonely mouth.

10:36.701 --> 10:38.567
You know, Al, this year,

10:38.567 --> 10:40.901
I was hoping
for something different.

10:40.901 --> 10:47.400
Uh-uh, Peg.
The socks stay on.

10:47.400 --> 10:50.400
No, Al. This year,
instead of sex,

10:50.400 --> 10:52.100
I want you
to tell me you love me.

10:57.701 --> 11:01.334
What if I do
take the socks off?

11:01.334 --> 11:02.801
I'm serious, Al.
I want to hear it.

11:02.801 --> 11:03.801
Yeah, right.

11:03.801 --> 11:05.000
Well, listen, Peg.

11:05.000 --> 11:06.467
I'm going to go
upstairs and wash up,

11:06.467 --> 11:08.000
but just to show you

11:08.000 --> 11:10.200
how really special
you are to me,

11:10.200 --> 11:14.133
tonight I'm
going to kiss you.

11:17.567 --> 11:22.033
Well, Mom, I've got all my cards
in this bag.

11:22.033 --> 11:24.901
Now, instead of dating
all the guys in here,

11:24.901 --> 11:27.267
which last year proved
to be almost impossible,

11:27.267 --> 11:29.100
this year, I'm going to
pick one lucky guy

11:29.100 --> 11:30.634
to represent
all of my admirers.

11:30.634 --> 11:31.701
Doesn't matter who it is.

11:31.701 --> 11:33.033
This is the one day

11:33.033 --> 11:34.033
everyone
has a fair chance,

11:34.033 --> 11:38.167
so pick one for me.

11:38.167 --> 11:39.167
Josh.

11:39.167 --> 11:44.601
He's really ugly.
Pick again.

11:44.601 --> 11:46.467
Sheldon?

11:46.467 --> 11:50.834
Okay, give me the bag.

11:50.834 --> 11:53.133
Okay.

11:53.133 --> 11:57.033
Pick the red one
with the star.

11:57.033 --> 11:58.400
Johnny.

11:58.400 --> 12:00.434
Oh, what luck.
The cutest guy in school.

12:00.434 --> 12:02.968
Oh, you sure know
how to pick a man.

12:06.467 --> 12:09.567
Well, all my Valentines
finally came in.

12:09.567 --> 12:10.968
I'm going upstairs
to open them.

12:10.968 --> 12:13.467
[BOTTLES CLANKING]

12:13.467 --> 12:15.968
Sounds kind of
like pop bottles.

12:15.968 --> 12:17.367
Well, they're not.

12:17.367 --> 12:18.868
They're paper.

12:18.868 --> 12:20.033
[CLANK]

12:20.033 --> 12:21.534
Uh, you know, Bud...

12:21.534 --> 12:23.501
You're my Valentine.

12:23.501 --> 12:28.734
Wow. Wait till I
go tell the guys.

12:28.734 --> 12:30.868
Well, speaking
of losers,

12:30.868 --> 12:33.334
I'm going to go through 
these excess Valentines.

12:33.334 --> 12:36.834
Let's see. "Fairest Kelly."

12:36.834 --> 12:41.667
"Beautiful Kelly."
"Kelly, my love. "

12:41.667 --> 12:43.167
"Dearest Bud"?

12:43.167 --> 12:45.167
Yes, yes! I knew it!

12:45.167 --> 12:47.901
Give it here.

12:52.167 --> 12:57.834
It's from some girl
named...April May June.

12:57.834 --> 13:00.334
She says she loves me,

13:00.334 --> 13:02.834
and she's coming over
to see me tonight.

13:02.834 --> 13:04.501
Oh, that's great, honey.

13:04.501 --> 13:07.334
Did you write
that card as a joke?

13:07.334 --> 13:09.067
No. Did you?

13:09.067 --> 13:12.033
Hey, you did write this,
didn't you, Kel?

13:12.033 --> 13:13.534
I mean, "April,
May, June"--

13:13.534 --> 13:19.467
those are all
words you know.

13:19.467 --> 13:21.667
Come on, Kel, just tell me,
because I've got a chance

13:21.667 --> 13:23.400
to go to the Bulls game
tonight with Joey.

13:23.400 --> 13:25.467
Gee, Bud. Dilemma, dilemma.

13:25.467 --> 13:27.467
Do you get all dressed up,

13:27.467 --> 13:29.701
stay here,
and look like an idiot,

13:29.701 --> 13:30.834
or go to the game,

13:30.834 --> 13:32.801
stand up the only date
you'll ever have,

13:32.801 --> 13:33.934
and look like an idiot?

13:33.934 --> 13:36.367
Hmm. Tough one for Bud.

13:36.367 --> 13:37.667
Well, I'm going
to got upstairs

13:37.667 --> 13:39.667
and get ready
for my real date.

13:39.667 --> 13:41.167
Did you write that,
Kel?

13:41.167 --> 13:42.667
Just say yes or no.

13:42.667 --> 13:43.767
No.

13:43.767 --> 13:45.367
Come on, Kel, really,
I know you did.

13:45.367 --> 13:46.834
Okay, yeah, I did.

13:46.834 --> 13:49.901
Oh, no, you didn't.
Really, Kel?

13:51.567 --> 13:57.367
Okay, Peg. No sense
in putting off the inevitable.

13:57.367 --> 13:59.000
Now, the kids
are upstairs,

13:59.000 --> 14:02.334
so we probably shouldn't
do it up there,

14:02.334 --> 14:04.801
what with your screaming
and everything.

14:04.801 --> 14:07.167
That was your fault, Al.

14:07.167 --> 14:09.834
You're the one
who turned the lights on.

14:15.234 --> 14:18.234
Hey, let's not throw stones
on this romantic night.

14:18.234 --> 14:19.234
Now, it's almost time,

14:19.234 --> 14:21.033
so why don't you
go down to the basement,

14:21.033 --> 14:22.167
blow up the air mattress?

14:22.167 --> 14:24.400
I'll pop some Tums
and be right down.

14:24.400 --> 14:28.601
I want to hear it, Al.

14:28.601 --> 14:30.501
I want to hear you say
"I love you."

14:30.501 --> 14:32.400
Not that again.

14:32.400 --> 14:33.601
Okay, Peg.

14:33.601 --> 14:35.400
Now, I know you didn't
think of this yourself.

14:35.400 --> 14:38.801
Now, where did this come from?
Phil? Oprah?

14:38.801 --> 14:40.767
Marcie.

14:40.767 --> 14:43.767
Oh, great. The only one
we can't turn off.

14:43.767 --> 14:46.801
Al, Steve and Marcie
not only say it,

14:46.801 --> 14:49.534
they mean it,
and they show it.

14:49.534 --> 14:52.234
Do you know what Marcie's
giving Steve tonight?

14:52.234 --> 14:54.734
A running start.

14:54.734 --> 14:57.234
No, she went
to Cakes a Poppin',

14:57.234 --> 14:59.234
and she's having herself
delivered to him.

14:59.234 --> 15:00.667
Then she's going
to pop out naked.

15:00.667 --> 15:02.167
I hope you're happy, Peg..

15:02.167 --> 15:05.334
I'll never
eat cake again.

15:05.334 --> 15:07.701
Al, if she can go to all that
trouble for Steve,

15:07.701 --> 15:10.534
the least you can do for me
is say "I love you."

15:14.968 --> 15:20.133
I'm not going downstairs
with you unless you say it.

15:20.133 --> 15:22.868
Withholding sex
from me, Peg? Oh no!

15:26.868 --> 15:28.501
Well, I guess I'll
just have to relax

15:28.501 --> 15:31.434
and have fun instead.

15:31.434 --> 15:34.434
Come on, Peg.
What's the big deal?

15:34.434 --> 15:36.501
You know I do.

15:36.501 --> 15:37.934
I just don't like
to say it.

15:37.934 --> 15:40.334
It...makes me sick.

15:40.334 --> 15:43.334
Well, it doesn't make me
sick to say it.

15:43.334 --> 15:44.834
I love you.

15:44.834 --> 15:46.868
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

15:46.868 --> 15:49.267
I'll be waiting upstairs.

15:52.968 --> 15:58.467
Time to reach out
and touch someone.

15:58.467 --> 16:00.901
Yeah, here we go.

16:00.901 --> 16:03.501
Ahem. Ahem.

16:07.434 --> 16:12.534
Hello. Yes, I'm calling about
the Marcie Rhoades cake.

16:12.534 --> 16:14.767
No, this is her husband.

16:14.767 --> 16:16.968
Yes, there's been
a change of plans.

16:16.968 --> 16:19.834
Instead of the address
she gave you...

16:19.834 --> 16:21.934
Do you have a pen?

16:27.200 --> 16:30.701
Bud, I don't know why
you're dressed like that.

16:30.701 --> 16:33.200
If you don't think
you really have a date,

16:33.200 --> 16:35.701
why did you pass up
a chance to go to the game?

16:35.701 --> 16:37.701
Look, maybe I just wanted
to spend the night

16:37.701 --> 16:40.200
watching the game
with my Dad.

16:40.200 --> 16:42.534
Why? What did I do?

16:42.534 --> 16:44.534
Oh, by the way, Dad,
Mom's upstairs cursing you.

16:44.534 --> 16:46.400
I'm late. I've got to go.

16:46.400 --> 16:48.567
Wait a second.
Kelly, come here a second.

16:51.601 --> 16:57.467
Now, you guys are,
what, in your teens?

16:57.467 --> 16:59.501
Something like that,
Dad, yeah.

16:59.501 --> 17:02.167
Well, you've known me
most of those years.

17:02.167 --> 17:03.968
How do you think your dad
feels about you?

17:03.968 --> 17:07.233
I mean, do you know
that your dad...

17:07.233 --> 17:08.534
Loves us?

17:08.534 --> 17:12.133
Yeah, that. You guys
know that, right?

17:12.133 --> 17:13.233
Sure.

17:13.233 --> 17:17.434
Dad, are you dying?

17:19.233 --> 17:22.233
Yes, but no one
seems to care.

17:22.233 --> 17:23.968
So, but, I mean,

17:23.968 --> 17:26.166
it's not important
for you to hear, uh...

17:26.166 --> 17:27.634
That you love us?

17:27.634 --> 17:28.801
Yes.

17:28.801 --> 17:31.400
Hey, you'll tell us
when you're ready.

17:31.400 --> 17:34.000
Yeah. Besides, we think
it would make a nice moment

17:34.000 --> 17:35.167
for when you're
old and feeble.

17:39.634 --> 17:41.534
Thank you.

17:45.267 --> 17:47.734
I'd be getting ready
if I were you, Bud.

17:47.734 --> 17:49.167
I'm not falling
for it, Kel.

17:57.133 --> 18:00.634
Look, Dad, I've got
a hot date coming.

18:00.634 --> 18:04.801
Get out.

18:04.801 --> 18:07.834
But the game's on.

18:07.834 --> 18:09.234
Dad...

18:09.234 --> 18:11.767
The way I see it,
if you left now,

18:11.767 --> 18:14.267
it would kind of be
like saying...

18:14.267 --> 18:16.467
you love me.

18:29.501 --> 18:31.667
So...how you doing?

18:34.033 --> 18:35.667
Aw, come on, Peg.

18:35.667 --> 18:37.300
People shouldn't have to say it.
It's unnecessary.

18:37.300 --> 18:41.567
I haven't cheated on you.
I haven't asked for my own room.

18:41.567 --> 18:45.667
I stayed through two kids
and your hotpants phase.

18:45.667 --> 18:46.767
Doesn't that say it?

18:46.767 --> 18:48.701
No.

18:48.701 --> 18:53.234
Well, then...could I have
my own room?

18:53.234 --> 18:54.234
No!

18:54.234 --> 18:56.267
Now, I want to hear it.

18:56.267 --> 18:57.267
Why?

18:57.267 --> 18:59.267
Because
it's nice to know.

18:59.267 --> 19:01.234
Now, I'll start.
I love you.

19:03.067 --> 19:05.734
Peg, this really makes
my stomach hurt.

19:05.734 --> 19:07.901
Well, then, you can
feel better real quick.

19:07.901 --> 19:08.934
Now, just say it.

19:10.634 --> 19:12.868
I...

19:12.868 --> 19:15.200
I have to go
to the bathroom.

19:24.334 --> 19:25.601
Thanks, Kel.

19:25.601 --> 19:27.567
Real funny joke.

19:27.567 --> 19:32.300
April May June...
you're so immature.

19:32.300 --> 19:37.434
Well, I hope you like
the itching powder in your bra.

19:37.434 --> 19:40.400
[DOORBELL RINGS]

19:44.367 --> 19:47.300
Hi, Bud. Did you get
my Valentine?

19:47.300 --> 19:48.667
I'm April May June.

19:51.734 --> 19:54.467
Yes, yes,
I vaguely remember.

19:54.467 --> 19:56.534
Come in, come in.

20:03.868 --> 20:07.067
So...you have
quite an unusual name.

20:07.067 --> 20:08.934
How did you get it?

20:08.934 --> 20:11.934
My parents are idiots.

20:11.934 --> 20:13.701
We have
a lot in common.

20:13.701 --> 20:17.501
So you want me to be
your Valentine, eh?

20:17.501 --> 20:19.567
Well, I saw you
around school,

20:19.567 --> 20:21.167
and I thought
you were kind of cute,

20:21.167 --> 20:23.033
but you never noticed me.

20:23.033 --> 20:24.467
You think I'm cute?

20:24.467 --> 20:26.100
Sure. All the girls do.

20:26.100 --> 20:28.734
Then why did I only get
one stinking Valentine?

20:31.100 --> 20:33.567
Sorry.
I meant thank you.

20:35.267 --> 20:37.901
Why are you scratching?

20:37.901 --> 20:40.300
It's this darn bra.

20:41.968 --> 20:43.133
That's better.

20:43.133 --> 20:48.133
And don't you hate it
when they ride up on you?

20:50.634 --> 20:53.734
Now, don't pull that upset
stomach routine with me, Al.

20:53.734 --> 20:56.734
Come out here and tell me
you love me.

20:56.734 --> 20:59.667
Are you going to tell me
or not?

21:03.667 --> 21:05.834
Okay, Peg,
I'm going to say it...

21:05.834 --> 21:07.601
but before I say it,

21:07.601 --> 21:09.667
I want to tell you
I really hate you for this.

21:13.467 --> 21:16.467
I don't want to do it.
I'm unhappy.

21:16.467 --> 21:20.667
My stomach is boiling,
my palms are sweating,

21:20.667 --> 21:22.667
and if you think you're getting
a jump after this,

21:22.667 --> 21:23.901
you're sadly mistaken.

21:25.834 --> 21:28.033
Of course, if you had
a brain in that huge head,

21:28.033 --> 21:29.534
you'd already know how I feel,

21:29.534 --> 21:32.601
but you want to hear it, fine.
This is what you want.

21:32.601 --> 21:35.834
It's your stinking lousy
Valentine's Day present,

21:35.834 --> 21:39.067
so here it is...

21:39.067 --> 21:40.834
I love you.

21:48.067 --> 21:51.000
Oh, Al!

21:51.000 --> 21:53.467
You didn't
have to say that.

21:58.234 --> 22:01.234
Gee, I only hope
that Steve and
Marcie

22:01.234 --> 22:04.234
are as happy as
we are right now.

22:04.234 --> 22:06.234
Well, I don't know about Steve,

22:06.234 --> 22:10.868
but, uh, Marcie's having
the night of her life.

22:13.167 --> 22:16.968
MARCIE:
* My funny valentine *

22:16.968 --> 22:20.534
* Sweet comic valentine *

22:20.534 --> 22:24.234
* You make me smile... *

